Tbis digression hus not been irrelevant; for, though the distinction between ‘hastati' ‘principes' and ‘triarii' or ‘piloni' was swept away when the army was remedelled by Marius, yet the centurions even in Caesar's time retained the titles which had a meaning only under the old system. Thus P. Sextius Baculus, the leading centuriones the twelfth legion, is called by Caesar (iii. 5, 5 a) ‘primi pili centurio,' and by a convenient, but illogical abbreviation, ‘primipilus’ (ii. agi 1)¹.
